THE WAY YOU ASK ‐‐

10:51.618 --> 10:52.886
SO THAT MEANS YES.

10:52.886 --> 10:54.454
MAGGIE, JIM ‐‐

10:54.454 --> 10:55.956
DAVID, AGAIN,
YOU HAVE HIS BACK.

10:55.956 --> 10:58.224
THIS IS A GREAT TRAIT,
BUT WAY OUT OF LINE RIGHT NOW.

10:58.224 --> 11:00.193
I HAVE MY BEST GUYS
RUNNING HER.

11:00.193 --> 11:02.268
I'LL KNOW
ALL ABOUT HER IN A FEW.

11:03.570 --> 11:05.806
NO NEED.
WE'VE ALREADY DONE THAT.

11:05.806 --> 11:08.174
NO, YOU DON'T HAVE ACCESS
TO THE SAME KIND OF INTEL I DO.

11:08.174 --> 11:09.142
REALLY?

11:09.142 --> 11:12.312
NO, YOU DON'T.
IT'S HIGHLY CLASSIFIED.

11:12.312 --> 11:14.948
I'LL KNOW HOW MANY FRECKLES
SHE HAS IN ABOUT 30 MINUTES.

11:14.948 --> 11:16.249
SHE'S BLACK.

11:16.249 --> 11:17.784
BLACK PEOPLE
HAVE FRECKLES.

11:19.285 --> 11:20.687
WHY WOULD YOU
NEED TO KNOW THIS?

11:20.687 --> 11:22.288
WHAT?
ABOUT HER FRECKLES?

11:22.288 --> 11:25.091
WHY WOULD YOU NEED TO KNOW
ABOUT CANDACE YOUNG?

11:25.091 --> 11:27.027
BECAUSE SOMETHING
IS GOING ON HERE,

11:27.027 --> 11:28.895
AND YOU'RE KEEPING ME
IN THE DARK!

11:28.895 --> 11:31.064
OKAY, JIM.

11:32.098 --> 11:34.701
I'M NOT THE ENEMY HERE.

11:34.701 --> 11:36.870
I'M A SOLVER OF PROBLEMS.

11:36.870 --> 11:40.440
I AM JUST TRYING TO HEAD OFF
ANY ISSUES

11:40.440 --> 11:42.442
THAT WE MAY HAVE WITH THIS WOMAN
BEFORE THEY START.

11:42.442 --> 11:45.111
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.
I'VE GOT IT UNDER CONTROL.

11:45.111 --> 11:46.847
I WILL HANDLE
MY PERSONAL LIFE.

11:46.847 --> 11:48.114
YOU HANDLE THE CAMPAIGN.

11:48.114 --> 11:49.983
YOUR PERSONAL LIFE
IS THE CAMPAIGN, JIM.

11:49.983 --> 11:51.718
THERE'S NO DISTINCTION
AT THIS POINT.

11:51.718 --> 11:52.853
YOU WANT TO WIN GOVERNOR?

11:52.853 --> 11:54.521
YOU BETTER TELL ME
WHAT'S GOING ON.

11:54.521 --> 11:56.557
I TOLD YOU I WILL HANDLE
CANDACE YOUNG.

11:56.557 --> 11:57.658
YOU BUTT OUT OF IT.

11:59.726 --> 12:01.267
OKAY. [ CLEARS THROAT ]
FINE.

12:01.267 --> 12:02.536
YOU KNOW, HAVE IT YOUR WAY.

12:02.536 --> 12:04.337
FINE.
BUT IF SOMETHING COMES UP

12:04.337 --> 12:06.406
IN THE MIDDLE OF THIS CAMPAIGN,
I WILL WALK. I MEAN IT.

12:06.406 --> 12:08.374
I DON'T SET MYSELF UP
FOR FAILURE,

12:08.374 --> 12:10.176
AND I ONLY ASSOCIATE
WITH WINNERS.

12:10.176 --> 12:12.513
WHO THE HELL IS
RUNNING FOR GOVERNOR
HERE, ME OR YOU?

12:12.513 --> 12:13.747
YOU THINK
THIS IS ABOUT YOU?

12:13.747 --> 12:14.748
YES.

12:14.748 --> 12:16.449
JIM CRYER,
I COULD GIVE A RAT'S ASS

12:16.449 --> 12:18.151
IF YOU WIN GOVERNOR
BASED ON MERIT.

12:18.151 --> 12:19.686
I HAVE A REPUTATION
AS A WINNER.

12:21.054 --> 12:24.424
MAGGIE, TRUST US.

12:24.424 --> 12:26.392
IT'S FINE.

12:28.762 --> 12:30.864
WE'RE GONNA HANDLE THIS.

12:31.898 --> 12:33.800
ALL RIGHT.

12:34.868 --> 12:38.672
SHE BETTER NOT SHOW UP
TO ANY MORE EVENTS UNANNOUNCED.

12:40.073 --> 12:42.308
SHE WON'T.

12:44.077 --> 12:46.112
OKAY. [ CLEARS THROAT ]

12:46.112 --> 12:48.582
I HAVE A MEETING.

12:48.582 --> 12:50.517
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

12:50.517 --> 12:54.788
UH, WE'LL BE MEETING
THE A.M.E. ZION PASTORS
TOMORROW MORNING.

12:54.788 --> 12:56.590
WE NEED THE AFRICAN‐AMERICAN
VOTE IN RECORD NUMBERS,

12:56.590 --> 12:58.391
SO, DAVID, I'M GONNA NEED YOU
TO RUN POINT ON THIS.

12:58.391 --> 13:00.093
WE ALSO NEED TO REISSUE
A STATEMENT

13:00.093 --> 13:01.267
IN SUPPORT OF THE POLICE

13:01.267 --> 13:03.269
CATCHING THE DRIVER
WHO HIT THAT LITTLE GIRL.

13:03.269 --> 13:04.938
THERE'S GONNA BE
A MARCH TOMORROW.

13:04.938 --> 13:06.239
YOU BOTH
SHOULD BE THERE.

13:06.239 --> 13:09.776
OH, AND I GOT THIS OUT
OF THE POLICE CHIEF EARLY.

13:09.776 --> 13:13.046
IT'LL BE RELEASED TOMORROW,
SO WE SHOULD BE HOLDING IT UP.

13:13.046 --> 13:14.781
IT'S GOOD
WE GOT IT FIRST.

13:14.781 --> 13:16.282
AND, UH,
WHAT IS THIS?

13:16.282 --> 13:18.118
THE MOTHER OF THE LITTLE GIRL
SAW THE DRIVER.

13:18.118 --> 13:20.654
THAT'S A COMPOSITE SKETCH.

13:20.654 --> 13:22.288
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

13:22.288 --> 13:24.525
[ DOOR OPENS ]

13:25.759 --> 13:26.760
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

13:26.760 --> 13:28.729
JIM.

13:33.600 --> 13:35.969
DAMN IT.

13:44.578 --> 13:46.412
Candace: YOUR MOM WAS SICK.
Jeffery: YEAH.

13:46.412 --> 13:48.615
YOU CRIED ALL THE WAY HOME.
I THOUGHT YOU'D BE ECSTATIC.

13:48.615 --> 13:50.183
YEAH, I AM.

13:50.183 --> 13:52.853
WHAT'S
HE DOING HERE?

13:52.853 --> 13:54.187
OH.

13:54.187 --> 13:55.589
SORRY WE'RE LATE.

14:01.301 --> 14:03.269
HI.
HI. HOW YOU DOING?

14:03.269 --> 14:04.605
HOW ARE YOU?
MWAH.

14:04.605 --> 14:07.307
SO, UM, I HAVE TO GO
AND GET CHANGED.

14:07.307 --> 14:11.311
I THOUGHT IT WOULD BE GREAT
IF YOU TWO WENT AND GOT COFFEE.

14:11.311 --> 14:12.312
CANDACE, I CAN'T.

14:12.312 --> 14:14.214
YES, YOU CAN.
ENJOY YOURSELF.

14:14.214 --> 14:15.949
HEY.

14:15.949 --> 14:17.818
[ DOOR OPENS ]

14:19.185 --> 14:20.253
HI.

14:21.287 --> 14:23.223
HI.

14:23.223 --> 14:26.426
YOU DON'T WANT TO DO THIS,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO.

14:27.460 --> 14:30.196
NO, IT'S ‐‐ IT'S FINE.

14:30.196 --> 14:31.832
YOU SURE?

14:34.167 --> 14:36.102
YEAH.

14:37.337 --> 14:39.205
I SAW A LITTLE PLACE
AROUND THE CORNER.

14:40.406 --> 14:42.008
YEAH?

14:45.211 --> 14:46.680
OKAY.

14:53.253 --> 14:55.956
Jim:
MAYBE. I GOT TO GO.

15:01.502 --> 15:03.136
ANY LUCK?

15:05.572 --> 15:07.373
NO.

15:08.675 --> 15:11.177
I CAN'T FIND
THAT DAMN CAR.

15:11.177 --> 15:13.213
I'VE BEEN THINKING.

15:13.213 --> 15:14.781
ABOUT WHAT?

15:14.781 --> 15:17.117
THE NEIGHBORHOOD WHERE
WYATT LEFT THE CAR,

15:17.117 --> 15:19.853
IT PROBABLY ENDED UP
IN A CHOP SHOP BY NOW.

15:19.853 --> 15:22.155
YEAH,
I THOUGHT ABOUT THAT, DAVID,

15:22.155 --> 15:24.290
BUT THAT WOULD BE
WAY TOO EASY.

15:24.290 --> 15:26.593
ONE CAN HOPE.

15:26.593 --> 15:29.362
WE NEED A LOT MORE THAN HOPE
RIGHT NOW.

15:29.362 --> 15:31.064
YES, I KNOW. I KNOW.
I KNOW.

15:31.064 --> 15:32.733
WELL,
WE DO HAVE YOUR PLAN.

15:32.733 --> 15:35.602
AND MY PLAN COULD WORK,
BUT IT HAS TO GO BY THE NUMBERS.

15:35.602 --> 15:37.037
AND THAT'S THE RISK IN IT.

15:37.037 --> 15:38.939
BELIEVE ME,
I UNDERSTAND, DAVID.

15:38.939 --> 15:41.742
IF YOU HAVE A BETTER PLAN,
THEN WE'LL GO WITH THAT.

15:41.742 --> 15:43.209
NO, I DON'T.
NO.

15:43.209 --> 15:47.480
WELL, THEN WE HAVE TO GO
WITH WHAT WE HAVE, DON'T WE?

15:47.480 --> 15:49.750
YES, WE DO,
BUT IT ‐‐ IT HAS TO ‐‐

15:49.750 --> 15:53.053
YEAH, I KNOW, I KNOW.
OR ALL OF IT WILL BE FOR NAUGHT.

15:53.053 --> 15:54.788
I UNDERSTAND.

15:54.788 --> 15:56.757
YOU KNOW HANNA HAS TO MAKE
THE FIRST MOVE

15:56.757 --> 15:58.458
FOR THIS TO WORK.
SHE WILL.

15:58.458 --> 15:59.626
SHE HAS TO.
SHE WILL.

15:59.626 --> 16:01.835
FROM WHAT I UNDERSTAND,
SHE'S FALLING APART.

16:01.835 --> 16:03.837
AND HOW
DO YOU KNOW THAT?

16:03.837 --> 16:07.240
I HAVE SOMEONE
IN THERE, OKAY?

16:07.240 --> 16:09.309
OKAY.

16:11.645 --> 16:14.480
SO WE HAVE A PLAN
FOR PROBLEM NUMBER ONE.

16:14.480 --> 16:15.649
YES.

16:15.649 --> 16:17.684
AND WE NEED A PLAN
FOR PROBLEM NUMBER TWO.

16:17.684 --> 16:19.820
CAN WE TALK
ABOUT CANDACE?

16:19.820 --> 16:22.756
WHAT DO YOU WANT TO
TALK ABOUT?

16:22.756 --> 16:25.291
SHE'S BECOME
A VERY DANGEROUS PROBLEM.

16:25.291 --> 16:26.426
I KNOW THAT.

16:27.561 --> 16:29.996
JIM, WE ARE NOT
JUST DREAMING ANYMORE.

16:29.996 --> 16:33.033
WE ARE AT THE DOOR.
YOU ARE RUNNING FOR GOVERNOR.

16:33.033 --> 16:35.502
DAVID, I UNDERSTAND THAT.

16:35.502 --> 16:37.638
I'M SURROUNDED BY POSTERS.
I GET IT.

16:37.638 --> 16:39.940
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
HER STOCK HAS GONE WAY UP,

16:39.940 --> 16:41.141
AND SHE KNOWS IT.

16:41.141 --> 16:43.109
I KNOW IT.

16:44.177 --> 16:46.279
ARE YOU STILL INVOLVED
WITH HER?

16:46.279 --> 16:50.116
ONLY FOR ABOUT
THE NEXT 18 YEARS.

16:50.116 --> 16:51.685
JIM!

16:51.685 --> 16:53.486
I KNOW. I KNOW.

16:53.486 --> 16:55.288
HOW THE HELL?

16:55.288 --> 16:59.192
JIM, HOW DO YOU MAKE
SUCH A STUPID MISTAKE?

16:59.192 --> 17:00.727
WHEN IT STARTED,
IT WAS MY MISTAKE.

17:00.727 --> 17:02.135
BUT NOW
IT'S CANDACE'S MISTAKE.

17:02.135 --> 17:03.303
AND WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

17:03.303 --> 17:04.838
SHE GOT MY DAUGHTER
INVOLVED.

17:04.838 --> 17:07.040
WHEN IT WAS JUST CANDACE AND I
PLAYING AROUND,

17:07.040 --> 17:08.108
THAT WAS A LOT OF FUN.

17:08.108 --> 17:09.876
THERE WERE THRILLS.

17:09.876 --> 17:11.311
BUT NOT ANYMORE.

17:11.311 --> 17:12.478
NOT ANYMORE.

17:12.478 --> 17:17.017
AMANDA IS SUING KATHERYN AND I
FOR HER INHERITANCE.

17:17.017 --> 17:19.520
CANDACE IS RESPONSIBLE
FOR THAT?

17:19.520 --> 17:22.556
COME ON. YOU THINK AMANDA WOULD
THINK OF THAT ALL ON HER OWN?

17:28.261 --> 17:29.930
CAN'T LET THAT HAPPEN.

17:29.930 --> 17:32.032
IT WON'T.

17:32.032 --> 17:34.601
SO, CAN YOU STALL
FOR TIME?

17:34.601 --> 17:36.537
OH, CANDACE
REALLY HAS IT OUT FOR ME

17:36.537 --> 17:38.572
EVER SINCE I WOULDN'T
HELP HER BROTHER.

17:38.572 --> 17:40.273
HELP HER BROTHER
DO WHAT?

17:40.273 --> 17:41.875
SHE WANTED HIM MOVED
TO A PRIVATE FACILITY.

17:41.875 --> 17:43.910
WELL, CAN'T GET INVOLVED
IN THAT.

17:43.910 --> 17:45.011
I'M NOT INVOLVED IN THAT.

17:45.011 --> 17:46.680
I'M NOT GOING TO DO THAT.
I DIDN'T DO IT.

17:46.680 --> 17:48.549
GOOD.

17:48.549 --> 17:51.017
BUT IT PISSED HER OFF.

17:55.989 --> 17:57.891
IT'S TIME TO CALL
THE MALONES.

18:00.466 --> 18:01.635
NO.

18:01.635 --> 18:02.936
YES.

18:02.936 --> 18:06.239
NO. DAVID.
NO, IT'S NOT THAT BAD.

18:08.308 --> 18:11.111
JIM, CANDACE HAS BECOME
A DANGEROUS PROBLEM

18:11.111 --> 18:13.479
THAT NEEDS TO BE SILENCED
FOR GOOD.

18:13.479 --> 18:15.481
I KNOW THAT.

18:15.481 --> 18:18.484
BUT THEY ARE RUTHLESS.

18:18.484 --> 18:21.922
THEY ARE NO LESS
THAN WHAT WE NEED.

18:21.922 --> 18:24.691
IT'S TOO EXTREME, DAVID.

18:26.426 --> 18:28.562
JIM, A YEAR AGO,

18:28.562 --> 18:31.665
YOU'D HAVE BEEN
THE FIRST ONE ON THE PHONE.

18:31.665 --> 18:34.901
SO APPARENTLY YOU HAVE
FEELINGS FOR THIS GAL.

18:34.901 --> 18:36.803
PLEASE.

18:36.803 --> 18:39.973
THEN CALL THE MALONES
NOW.

18:39.973 --> 18:41.875
I HAVE TO GET AMANDA
OUT OF THE APARTMENT FIRST.

18:41.875 --> 18:43.777
I DON'T WANT THEM HAVING
ANYTHING TO DO WITH HER.

18:43.777 --> 18:44.978
NO.

18:44.978 --> 18:47.047
JIM, YOU GET CANDACE
OUT OF THE APARTMENT,

18:47.047 --> 18:49.650
AND YOU CALL THEM NOW.

19:03.870 --> 19:07.007
YOU'RE NOT EATING.

19:07.007 --> 19:09.042
I TOLD YOU
I WASN'T HUNGRY.

19:09.042 --> 19:11.678
I KNOW. BUT YOU
HAVE TO EAT SOMETHING.

19:11.678 --> 19:13.814
WHY DO YOU CARE?

19:13.814 --> 19:15.649
YOU GOT TO KEEP
YOUR STRENGTH UP.

19:15.649 --> 19:17.518
DON'T WANT TO FAINT
BEFORE THE MIRACLE.

19:19.853 --> 19:21.622
YOU A MAN OF FAITH?

19:23.890 --> 19:25.626
SOMEWHAT.

19:25.626 --> 19:27.160
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

19:28.995 --> 19:31.231
IT MEANS THAT I KNOW
THERE'S SOMETHING UP THERE.

19:31.231 --> 19:32.699
I JUST DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT IS.

19:32.699 --> 19:34.134
HIS NAME IS JESUS.

19:34.134 --> 19:36.570
HMM. MAYBE.

19:38.471 --> 19:40.473
JUST NOT A RELIGIOUS GUY.

19:40.473 --> 19:43.209
I'M NOT A RELIGIOUS PERSON,
EITHER.

19:43.209 --> 19:44.878
I'M A SPIRITUAL PERSON

19:44.878 --> 19:47.814
WHO BELIEVES IN GOD
WITH ALL MY HEART.

19:47.814 --> 19:49.583
YOU BELIEVE
HE'LL SAVE YOUR SON?

19:49.583 --> 19:51.051
YES, I DO.

19:51.051 --> 19:52.986
AND WHAT IF HE DOESN'T?

19:52.986 --> 19:55.455
HMM.

19:57.257 --> 20:00.193
IF HE DOESN'T, THEN I...

20:00.193 --> 20:03.770
WOULD LIKE TO THINK
THAT I WOULD...

20:03.770 --> 20:06.439
DO WHAT DAVID DID.

20:07.741 --> 20:08.775
DAVID?

20:10.410 --> 20:12.145
THE KING IN THE BIBLE.

20:13.279 --> 20:17.083
WROTE SOME OF THE MOST BEAUTIFUL
PSALMS IN THE BIBLE.

20:19.753 --> 20:23.189
HE LOST HIS SON...

20:23.189 --> 20:27.694
AND HE WENT TO THE TEMPLE
AND PRAISED GOD.

20:29.229 --> 20:30.631
PRAISED GOD?

20:30.631 --> 20:31.898
MM‐HMM.

20:31.898 --> 20:35.235
HE TRUSTED GOD THAT MUCH.

20:35.235 --> 20:40.807
HE LOVED GOD SO MUCH...

20:40.807 --> 20:43.744
THAT HE PRAISED HIM...

20:43.744 --> 20:44.945
AND PRAISED HIM SO HARD

20:44.945 --> 20:47.047
THAT HE DANCED
RIGHT OUT OF HIS CLOTHES.

20:47.047 --> 20:49.149
WOW.

20:49.149 --> 20:53.386
'CAUSE NO MATTER WHAT,
HE'S STILL GOD.

20:53.386 --> 20:57.558
YOU SAID YOU'D LIKE TO THINK
THAT YOU'D DO WHAT HE DID?

20:57.558 --> 20:58.992
YOU'RE NOT SURE?

21:02.503 --> 21:06.106
I BELIEVE IN MY SOUL
THAT I WOULD DO THAT.

21:09.009 --> 21:14.715
BUT I'M A HUMAN PERSON HAVING
A SPIRITUAL EXPERIENCE.

21:14.715 --> 21:16.617
WELL, I'M TRYING TO.

21:18.184 --> 21:23.757
I MEAN, ONE MINUTE I'M CRYING
AND ONE MINUTE I'M ANGRY,

21:23.757 --> 21:28.161
AND THEN ANOTHER MINUTE
I'M TRYING TO HOLD ON.

21:33.567 --> 21:35.301
BUT I DON'T KNOW.

21:36.937 --> 21:39.105
AND THIS...

21:39.105 --> 21:42.576
OH. MY FLESH...

21:45.512 --> 21:49.550
MY HEART WOULD BE BROKEN.

21:51.718 --> 21:53.319
[ GROANS ]

21:53.319 --> 21:55.556
OH.

21:55.556 --> 21:57.658
BYRON, WHY ARE
WE TALKING ABOUT THIS?

21:57.658 --> 21:59.059
I KNOW, I KNOW.

22:01.602 --> 22:03.737
SORRY. I JUST WANT YOU
TO LOOK AT ALL SIDES OF THIS.

22:03.737 --> 22:05.171
I AM.

22:05.171 --> 22:06.740
GOOD.

22:08.474 --> 22:10.911
I'VE BEEN AN OFFICER
FOR OVER 20 YEARS.

22:10.911 --> 22:12.478
I'VE SEEN A LOT OF THINGS.

22:12.478 --> 22:14.948
A LOT OF PEOPLE
LOSE LOVED ONES.

22:14.948 --> 22:18.418
YEAH, BUT HAVE
YOU EVER SEEN A MIRACLE?

22:19.720 --> 22:23.824
IF BY THAT YOU MEAN SOME THINGS
I CAN'T EXPLAIN, SURE.

22:23.824 --> 22:25.792
LIKE WHAT?

22:29.930 --> 22:32.966
BOY SHOT NINE TIMES,

22:32.966 --> 22:35.536
LEFT FOR DEAD.

22:35.536 --> 22:38.271
AMBULANCE CALLED IN.

22:38.271 --> 22:40.807
GET TO THE HOSPITAL,

22:40.807 --> 22:43.644
OPENS HIS EYES
AND ASKS FOR HIS MOTHER.

22:45.378 --> 22:48.515
THAT'S WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT
RIGHT THERE.

22:48.515 --> 22:52.786
THAT'S THE KIND OF GOD
I SERVE.

22:52.786 --> 22:55.822
I NEED ONE OF THOSE.
HMM.

22:55.822 --> 22:59.626
WELL, HANNA, IF ANYONE SEEMS
TO HAVE THE FAITH TO GET IT...

23:01.201 --> 23:03.637
...IT'S YOU.

23:03.637 --> 23:06.673
I HOPE SO.

23:08.208 --> 23:09.442
EAT.

23:09.442 --> 23:10.811
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:10.811 --> 23:12.345
NO, THANK YOU.

23:12.345 --> 23:14.515
BUT THANKS FOR TRYING.

23:14.515 --> 23:16.382
YOU SURE?
YEAH.

23:16.382 --> 23:18.384
I GOT TO GET BACK
TO HIS SIDE.

23:18.384 --> 23:20.587
OKAY. LISTEN, I'M GONNA COME
BACK LATER IF THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

23:20.587 --> 23:22.022
OH, BYRON...

23:22.022 --> 23:23.557
COME ON NOW.
I'M JUST GONNA COME,

23:23.557 --> 23:25.391
PICK YOU UP AFTER
VISITING HOURS ARE OVER,

23:25.391 --> 23:26.660
TAKE YOU HOME.
THAT'S IT.

23:27.761 --> 23:28.995
OKAY?

23:28.995 --> 23:31.732
OKAY.

23:31.732 --> 23:33.834
OKAY.

23:33.834 --> 23:36.202
SEE YOU AT 8:00.

23:39.205 --> 23:41.307
OKAY.

23:50.717 --> 23:52.886
YOU'RE NOT THE SAME
WHEN YOU'RE NOT DRINKING.

23:52.886 --> 23:54.387
HOW SO?

23:54.387 --> 23:55.756
You're quiet.

23:56.890 --> 23:59.926
OH, I'M SORRY.

23:59.926 --> 24:02.636
YEAH, IT'S JUST
BEEN A LONG DAY.

24:02.636 --> 24:04.470
YOUR MOTHER?

24:04.470 --> 24:06.707
WHAT?

24:06.707 --> 24:09.009
CANDACE TOLD ME
THAT YOU MET WITH HER TODAY.

24:10.043 --> 24:12.579
YES, MY MOTHER.

24:12.579 --> 24:13.614
LET ME GUESS.

24:13.614 --> 24:16.149
SHE'S NOT HAPPY
WITH YOU COMING OUT.

24:16.149 --> 24:17.884
OH, SHE TOLD YOU
THAT, TOO?

24:17.884 --> 24:20.120
NO, YOU TOLD ME AT THE CLUB
THE OTHER NIGHT,

24:20.120 --> 24:22.523
BUT YOU DON'T REMEMBER
'CAUSE YOU WERE DRINKING.

24:22.523 --> 24:25.391
CANDACE CALLED ME TODAY AND SAID
TO COME TALK TO YOU, SO...

24:25.391 --> 24:28.562
WELL, I'M SORRY.
I'M ‐‐ I'M FINE.

24:28.562 --> 24:31.331
IT'S OKAY.

24:31.331 --> 24:33.466
JEFFERY, I WORK
WITH AN ORGANIZATION

24:33.466 --> 24:36.136
CALLED THE HOMEFRONT WELL.
HAVE YOU HEARD OF IT?

24:36.136 --> 24:39.105
YEAH, YOU GUYS WORK WITH KIDS
THAT ARE IN THE STREETS, RIGHT?

24:39.105 --> 24:42.142
YEAH, BUT A LOT OF THESE KIDS
WERE PUT OUT AS YOUNG AS 12

24:42.142 --> 24:43.944
BECAUSE THEY WERE GAY.

24:43.944 --> 24:45.311
REALLY?

24:45.311 --> 24:46.913
YEAH.

24:49.349 --> 24:51.084
YOU SHOULD MEET
SOME OF THEM.

24:52.786 --> 24:54.120
THEIR STORIES
ARE INCREDIBLE,

24:54.120 --> 24:55.756
AND THEY'RE ‐‐
THEY'RE THE BEST KIDS.

24:57.490 --> 24:59.626
BUT THEY WERE HATED
BY THEIR PARENTS.

25:01.267 --> 25:04.170
HOW COULD A PARENT
HATE THEIR CHILD?

25:04.170 --> 25:06.773
YOU'D BE SURPRISED.

25:09.175 --> 25:11.477
SHE LOOKS AT ME
LIKE SHE HATES ME.

25:11.477 --> 25:12.846
YOUR MOTHER?

25:12.846 --> 25:14.681
YEAH.

25:14.681 --> 25:17.183
I'M SORRY.

25:18.919 --> 25:21.387
THE THING I JUST ‐‐
I WANT HER TO UNDERSTAND

25:21.387 --> 25:22.789
THAT THIS ISN'T A CHOICE.

25:22.789 --> 25:25.458
WELL, SOMETIMES
THEY NEVER UNDERSTAND.

25:25.458 --> 25:26.893
I'M A REALLY NICE GUY,

25:26.893 --> 25:29.930
BUT PEOPLE LIKE THAT
GET UNDER MY SKIN BIG‐TIME.

25:31.798 --> 25:34.367
I'M SORRY.
UM, CAN WE CHANGE THE SUBJECT?

25:34.367 --> 25:36.637
IT'S OKAY. WE DON'T
HAVE TO TALK ABOUT THIS.

25:36.637 --> 25:37.804
I KNOW HOW HARD IT IS.

25:37.804 --> 25:39.773
I JUST CANNOT STAND
PEOPLE LIKE THAT.

25:39.773 --> 25:40.941
THEY MAKE ME SO ANGRY.

25:40.941 --> 25:42.142
YOU DON'T DESERVE THAT.

25:42.142 --> 25:44.144
YEAH.

25:44.144 --> 25:46.012
YEAH, UM, I HAVE TO GO.

25:46.012 --> 25:47.380
JEFFERY.
SORRY. SORRY.

25:47.380 --> 25:48.414
I'M SORRY.

25:48.414 --> 25:50.383
YEAH, I'LL ‐‐
I'LL TALK TO YOU LATER.

25:52.252 --> 25:54.320
DAMN IT.

26:02.736 --> 26:04.671
DID YOU POLISH
THE SILVER?

26:04.671 --> 26:06.372
UH, YES, MA'AM, I DID.

26:06.372 --> 26:08.509
WELL, DO IT AGAIN.

26:08.509 --> 26:11.277
THIS TIME,
USE THE OTHER TEA SERVERS.

26:11.277 --> 26:13.514
YES, MA'AM.

26:13.514 --> 26:16.382
I SURE HOPE HANNA
GETS BACK SOON.

26:16.382 --> 26:17.851
I KNOW. ME TOO.

26:17.851 --> 26:19.720
Veronica: KAT.

26:19.720 --> 26:22.088
HI.
HI.

26:22.088 --> 26:24.558
WHY DID MAGGIE
WANT TO SEE US?

26:24.558 --> 26:25.859
I DON'T KNOW.

26:25.859 --> 26:27.561
HAD ME
RUSHING OVER HERE.

26:27.561 --> 26:28.662
IS SHE HERE YET?

26:28.662 --> 26:31.231
NO, SHE CALLED TO SAY
SHE'S ON HER WAY.

26:31.231 --> 26:32.799
OH.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

26:32.799 --> 26:35.135
WELL, IF YOU MEAN
AT THIS MOMENT,

26:35.135 --> 26:37.838
I AM TRYING TO GET ALONG
WITHOUT HANNA.

26:37.838 --> 26:40.841
[ CHUCKLES ] WELL,
THAT'S NOT WHAT I MEANT.

26:40.841 --> 26:42.943
BUT CAN CELINE
NOT KEEP UP?

26:42.943 --> 26:44.377
NO.
[ CHUCKLES ]

26:44.377 --> 26:47.280
WELL, WHEN IS HANNA
COMING BACK?

26:47.280 --> 26:48.749
NOT SOON ENOUGH.

26:48.749 --> 26:50.551
WHAT IS SHE SAYING?

26:50.551 --> 26:52.719
I HAVEN'T SPOKEN TO HER.

26:52.719 --> 26:54.555
WHY NOT?

26:54.555 --> 26:56.590
YOU KNOW WHY NOT.

26:59.025 --> 27:01.101
COME ON.

27:01.101 --> 27:03.436
LET'S GO HAVE SOME TEA
ON THE LANAI.

27:03.436 --> 27:04.470
THAT OKAY?

27:04.470 --> 27:05.739
THAT SOUNDS WONDERFUL.

27:05.739 --> 27:07.941
She listens
to everything.

27:09.843 --> 27:10.944
CELINE!

27:10.944 --> 27:12.478
Celine:
YES, MA'AM?

27:12.478 --> 27:15.048
CAN YOU BRING US SOME TEA
ON THE LANAI, PLEASE?

27:15.048 --> 27:16.683
YES, MA'AM.

27:16.683 --> 27:19.953
AND WHEN MS. DAY GETS HERE,
PLEASE SEND HER OUT TO US.

27:19.953 --> 27:22.355
YES, MA'AM.

27:22.355 --> 27:25.191
KATHERYN, I WOULDN'T HAVE
SOMEONE WORKING FOR ME

27:25.191 --> 27:27.427
THAT I COULDN'T
SPEAK FREELY AROUND.

27:27.427 --> 27:28.895
I UNDERSTAND THAT.

27:28.895 --> 27:31.331
THEN WHY
DON'T YOU FIRE HER?

27:31.331 --> 27:35.435
YOU'RE THE ONE THAT FIRES
EVERYBODY AT THE DROP OF A DIME.

27:35.435 --> 27:36.770
YOU KNOW THAT OLD SAYING

27:36.770 --> 27:39.506
"KEEP YOUR FRIENDS CLOSE
AND YOUR ENEMIES CLOSER"?

27:39.506 --> 27:42.375
SOMETIMES IT'S MORE POWERFUL
TO KEEP SOMEBODY AROUND.

27:42.375 --> 27:43.309
WHATEVER.

27:43.309 --> 27:45.746
WHAT'S GOING ON
WITH HANNA?

27:45.746 --> 27:47.413
JIM THINKS
SHE DOESN'T TRUST ME.

27:47.413 --> 27:48.481
WHAT?

27:48.481 --> 27:50.984
HE THINKS SHE'S GOING
TO GO TO THE POLICE.

27:50.984 --> 27:52.986
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

27:52.986 --> 27:55.055
I HONESTLY DON'T KNOW.

27:56.256 --> 27:58.992
SHE'S BEEN RIGHT HERE
BY MY SIDE.

27:58.992 --> 28:01.067
YOU TALK AS IF
SHE DOESN'T WORK FOR YOU.

28:01.067 --> 28:02.603
I KNOW HER.

28:02.603 --> 28:04.671
HOW WELL CAN YOU KNOW HER?
SHE'S YOUR MAID.

28:04.671 --> 28:09.610
I MEAN, YOU CAN NEVER
REALLY TRULY KNOW SOMEONE

28:09.610 --> 28:10.944
WHO WORKS FOR YOU.

28:10.944 --> 28:12.946
YOU KNOW THAT, KATHERYN.

28:12.946 --> 28:15.549
SHE'S DIFFERENT, VERONICA.

28:15.549 --> 28:18.251
[ DOOR OPENS ]
SHE JUST IS.

28:20.587 --> 28:21.888
YOUR TEA, MA'AM.

28:21.888 --> 28:23.089
THANK YOU.

28:23.089 --> 28:25.526
YOU'RE WELCOME.

28:25.526 --> 28:27.127
[ DOOR OPENS ]

28:27.127 --> 28:28.862
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
DRINK THAT, ARE YOU?

28:28.862 --> 28:30.296
WHAT?
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

28:30.296 --> 28:32.533
I'M NOT DRINKING THAT.

28:32.533 --> 28:34.935
SHE WOULDN'T DARE.

28:34.935 --> 28:37.103
I DON'T KNOW, KATHERYN.

28:38.271 --> 28:40.373
ANYWAY...

28:44.210 --> 28:45.245
[ SIGHS ]

28:45.245 --> 28:46.880
I WANT TO HAVE BENNY MOVED.

28:46.880 --> 28:48.248
YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

28:48.248 --> 28:50.751
I KNOW, BUT THE CARE
HE'S GETTING THERE IS AWFUL.

28:50.751 --> 28:52.485
THAT MAY BE SO,
BUT IF YOU MOVE HIM,

28:52.485 --> 28:54.821
YOU WILL OPEN A CAN OF WORMS
THAT YOU JUST DON'T ‐‐

28:54.821 --> 28:57.691
JIM HAS ALREADY SAID THAT.

28:57.691 --> 28:59.626
HE'S A GOOD BOY, VERONICA.

28:59.626 --> 29:02.268
YOU MET HIM.

29:02.268 --> 29:04.437
HANNA IS A FRIEND.

29:04.437 --> 29:06.272
KATHERYN,
YOU CAN'T MOVE HIM.

29:06.272 --> 29:08.308
[ DOOR OPENS ]
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

29:08.308 --> 29:09.743
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

29:09.743 --> 29:11.512
HELLO, LADIES.
HELLO.

29:11.512 --> 29:12.979
YOU HAVE
A LOVELY HOME.

29:12.979 --> 29:14.247
WELL, THANK YOU.

29:14.247 --> 29:15.982
HELLO,
MRS. HARRINGTON.

29:15.982 --> 29:18.251
HI.

29:18.251 --> 29:19.986
HAVE A SEAT.

29:19.986 --> 29:21.487
THANK YOU.

29:24.090 --> 29:25.425
SO, WHAT'S GOING ON?

29:25.425 --> 29:28.261
WELL [CLEARS THROAT]
WE HAVE A BIT OF AN ISSUE.

29:28.261 --> 29:29.362
TELL.

29:29.362 --> 29:31.832
I MET WITH YOUR HUSBANDS
EARLIER,

29:31.832 --> 29:34.935
AND THEN I MET WITH
SOME OF MY PRIVATE EYES.

29:34.935 --> 29:37.871
I JUST NEED A LITTLE HELP
WITH SOMETHING.

29:37.871 --> 29:39.606
OKAY.

29:41.808 --> 29:43.309
WHO'S CANDACE YOUNG?

29:49.015 --> 29:52.118
REALLY?
SILENCE JUST LIKE YOUR HUSBANDS.

29:52.118 --> 29:55.155
SHE'S A NON‐FACTOR.

29:55.155 --> 29:57.824
OKAY, WELL, NON‐FACTORS

29:57.824 --> 30:00.193
CAN STILL BE NON‐STARTERS
OF CAMPAIGNS.

30:00.193 --> 30:02.603
WHAT HAS SHE DONE?

30:02.603 --> 30:04.137
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
SHE'S DONE SOMETHING?

30:04.137 --> 30:06.172
I JUST ASSUMED SHE HAD.

30:06.172 --> 30:07.808
YOU'RE LYING.

30:07.808 --> 30:10.811
I DON'T APPRECIATE
YOU CALLING ME A LIAR.

30:10.811 --> 30:13.313
COOL YOUR HEELS.

30:15.281 --> 30:17.784
YOU KNOW, THEY'RE NICE,
BY THE WAY.

30:17.784 --> 30:19.285
GOOD COLOR, NO FLASH.

30:19.285 --> 30:23.156
MS. DAY, DO YOU HAVE
BUSINESS WITH US OR NOT?

30:24.357 --> 30:25.626
BROUGHT YOU A GIFT.

30:25.626 --> 30:27.661
AND WHAT,
PRAY TELL, IS THAT?

30:27.661 --> 30:30.330
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

30:30.330 --> 30:32.633
WELL, I HAVE
VERY POWERFUL FRIENDS.

30:32.633 --> 30:36.837
THEY HAVE ACCESS
TO ALL KINDS OF INFORMATION.

30:36.837 --> 30:40.741
CANDACE YOUNG, THE DAUGHTER
OF HANNA YOUNG, YOUR MAID,

30:40.741 --> 30:43.443
TROUBLED YOUTH,
BABY AT 17,

30:43.443 --> 30:45.679
WHEREABOUTS
OF THE CHILD ARE UNKNOWN.

30:45.679 --> 30:49.282
THE CHILD'S FATHER,
QUINCY MAXWELL ‐‐

30:49.282 --> 30:51.384
I KNOW THAT NAME.
NO.

30:51.384 --> 30:54.855
NO, YOU KNOW
JUAN MAXWELL.

30:54.855 --> 30:56.156
YOU DEFENDED HIS BROTHER.

30:56.156 --> 30:58.358
GOT HIM OFF ON CHARGES
OF DRUG POSSESSION.

30:58.358 --> 31:00.527
HE WAS MURDERED
A YEAR LATER.

31:00.527 --> 31:03.504
QUINCY MAXWELL,
THE BABY'S FATHER, AGAIN,

31:03.504 --> 31:05.005
IS IN PRISON FOR LIFE.

31:05.005 --> 31:07.841
CHARGES OF MURDER,
LARCENY, GRAND LARCENY,

31:07.841 --> 31:10.544
ATTEMPTED MURDER,
BURGLARY, YOU NAME IT.

31:10.544 --> 31:12.546
I SPOKE
TO THE ARRESTING OFFICER,

31:12.546 --> 31:15.248
AND IT SEEMS THEY WERE GIVEN
A TIP TO HIS CRIMES

31:15.248 --> 31:17.518
BY AN UNNAMED ACCOMPLICE.

31:17.518 --> 31:19.753
NOW, HE WOULDN'T
GIVE UP THE NAME,

31:19.753 --> 31:21.922
BUT I THINK
IT WAS CANDACE YOUNG,

31:21.922 --> 31:26.827
THE SAME CANDACE YOUNG
WHO POSTED AN AD ON A WEBSITE.

31:26.827 --> 31:32.265
SHE WAS A PROSTITUTE,
SO SHE GOT LOTS OF PHONE CALLS.

31:32.265 --> 31:34.868
BUT, YOU KNOW,
THERE WAS ONE PHONE CALL

31:34.868 --> 31:36.336
THAT STRUCK ME AS ODD.

31:36.336 --> 31:41.441
SHE WAS CALLED 17 TIMES
BY AN UNTRACEABLE TracFone,

31:41.441 --> 31:44.410
OR ‐‐ OR SO PEOPLE THINK.

31:46.647 --> 31:50.016
IT SEEMS THAT PHONE
WAS PURCHASED

31:50.016 --> 31:54.588
A FEW WEEKS PRIOR BY YOUR MAID,
CELINE GONZALES.

31:54.588 --> 31:58.525
THIS ALL STARTING
TO COME TOGETHER FOR YOU?

32:00.193 --> 32:03.036
WHY ARE YOU
TELLING US THIS?

32:03.036 --> 32:06.039
YOU'RE THINKING ABOUT
QUITTING THE CAMPAIGN?

32:06.039 --> 32:07.608
[ SCOFFS ] NO, HONEY.

32:07.608 --> 32:09.676
IF YOU THINK THIS
IS ENOUGH TO MAKE ME QUIT,

32:09.676 --> 32:11.011
YOU'RE SADLY MISTAKEN.

32:11.011 --> 32:13.246
YOU SHOULD HAVE SEEN THE LAST
GOVERNOR'S DIRTY LAUNDRY.

32:13.246 --> 32:15.448
MAKES JIM'S ESCAPADES
LOOK LIKE A NURSERY RHYME.

32:17.618 --> 32:21.454
SO, HONEY, WHY ARE YOU
GIVING US THIS INFORMATION?

32:21.454 --> 32:23.590
INTEL.

32:27.594 --> 32:31.431
INTEL THAT CAN HELP
ELIMINATE.

32:33.834 --> 32:36.903
SOMETIMES WHEN YOU'VE GOT A DOG
THAT'S OUT OF CONTROL,

32:36.903 --> 32:39.239
YOU UNLEASH A BIGGER DOG
TO CONTROL HIM.

32:42.275 --> 32:46.379
NOW, THIS BOY SEEMS TO HAVE
A BONE TO PICK WITH MS. YOUNG,

32:46.379 --> 32:50.951
SO IF HE WAS OUT,
PERHAPS HE COULD.

32:50.951 --> 32:53.987
I MEAN, OF COURSE, I CAN'T PULL
THOSE KINDS OF STRINGS,

32:53.987 --> 32:57.991
BUT IF A FANTASTIC LAWYER
WITH A STELLAR REPUTATION

32:57.991 --> 33:02.302
WERE TO PAY HIM A VISIT
AND TELL HIM ALL THAT SHE KNOWS,

33:02.302 --> 33:06.039
THEN PERHAPS HE COULD GIVE
HER SOME INFORMATION

33:06.039 --> 33:10.043
THAT WOULD HELP HIM
GET OUT ONE DAY SOON...

33:12.445 --> 33:15.381
...AND HELP US SOLVE
OUR PROBLEM.

33:17.350 --> 33:20.186
DO EITHER OF YOU LADIES
KNOW OF AN AMAZING LAWYER

33:20.186 --> 33:24.124
THAT COULD PAY
A VERY PRIVATE VISIT

33:24.124 --> 33:26.660
TO THIS YOUNG MAN
THAT I COULD ARRANGE?

33:29.129 --> 33:30.931
I THINK I DO.

33:32.866 --> 33:35.401
GOOD.

33:37.037 --> 33:39.372
IS THIS CHAMOMILE?
YES.

33:39.372 --> 33:41.174
OH, LET ME POUR.

33:41.174 --> 33:42.509
HMM. THANK YOU.

33:49.049 --> 33:50.383
ENJOY.

33:56.122 --> 33:58.391
THANK YOU.

34:00.326 --> 34:01.301
MMM.

34:04.004 --> 34:05.639
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:12.445 --> 34:14.848
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

34:14.848 --> 34:17.150
[ VENTILATOR HISSING ]

34:59.425 --> 35:01.101
HANNA.

35:04.771 --> 35:05.706
HANNA.

35:18.484 --> 35:20.587
HI.

35:20.587 --> 35:23.624
HOW ARE YOU?

35:30.897 --> 35:32.966
I'M OKAY.

35:36.537 --> 35:38.138
HOW'S HE DOING?

35:38.138 --> 35:39.606
OH.

35:41.808 --> 35:44.678
I WISH PEOPLE WOULD
STOP ASKING ME THAT.

35:44.678 --> 35:47.147
I'M SORRY.

35:47.147 --> 35:50.717
I'M JUST REALLY WORRIED
ABOUT YOUR SON.

35:50.717 --> 35:53.319
HMM.

35:55.055 --> 35:57.357
HOW IS YOUR SON?

36:01.334 --> 36:03.804
HE'S OKAY.

36:05.005 --> 36:08.374
HOW'S HE HOLDING UP?

36:11.044 --> 36:13.346
HE'S GOOD.

36:13.346 --> 36:15.682
IS HE?

36:15.682 --> 36:17.918
YES.

36:19.620 --> 36:21.487
WHY DO YOU ASK?

36:22.823 --> 36:25.859
DON'T PLAY GAMES WITH ME.

36:25.859 --> 36:27.828
HANNA ‐‐

36:27.828 --> 36:31.264
HE SAID HE HIT SOMEBODY.

36:31.264 --> 36:35.569
THEN YOUR HUSBAND TRIED
TO MAKE ME THINK I WAS CRAZY,

36:35.569 --> 36:37.470
LIKE HE DIDN'T SAY IT.

36:39.272 --> 36:42.643
YOU WERE STANDING
RIGHT THERE.

36:44.878 --> 36:46.613
WYATT IS MY SON, HANNA.

36:46.613 --> 36:48.181
AND BENNY IS MINE.

36:48.181 --> 36:49.883
[ Voice breaking ]
THEN LET ME HELP YOUR SON.

36:49.883 --> 36:51.718
NO.

36:51.718 --> 36:54.320
HANNA,
YOU HAVE TO TRUST ME.

36:57.591 --> 36:59.359
WHY?

37:02.135 --> 37:05.705
YOU TELL ME THE TRUTH NOW.

37:05.705 --> 37:07.440
HANNA ‐‐

37:07.440 --> 37:09.442
[ Voice breaking ]
MRS. CRYER,

37:09.442 --> 37:12.478
I'M GONNA ASK YOU THIS
ONE TIME.

37:12.478 --> 37:15.982
[ BEEPING AND HISSING CONTINUE ]

37:15.982 --> 37:18.852
DID WYATT DO THIS?

37:23.524 --> 37:26.593
I CAME HERE TO OFFER HELP
FOR YOUR SON.

37:30.731 --> 37:33.133
DID HE DO IT?

37:40.240 --> 37:43.744
I CAME HERE...

37:43.744 --> 37:45.679
TO OFFER HELP
FOR YOUR SON.

37:45.679 --> 37:47.881
JUST TELL ME.

38:10.911 --> 38:18.451
I CAME HERE TO OFFER...
TO HELP YOUR SON.

38:22.923 --> 38:25.692
JESUS CHRIST.

38:31.364 --> 38:33.199
I DON'T WANT YOUR HELP.

38:33.199 --> 38:35.501
HANNA...

38:38.672 --> 38:40.541
PLEASE LEAVE.

38:40.541 --> 38:42.175
HANNA, I ‐‐

38:42.175 --> 38:43.677
AND I QUIT.

38:43.677 --> 38:45.746
HANNA, WAIT A SECOND.

38:45.746 --> 38:50.416
PLEASE...LEAVE.

38:50.416 --> 38:51.985
HANNA, I...

39:13.814 --> 39:14.848
[ Sobs ] HANNA.

39:49.683 --> 39:51.284
ARE YOU CRAZY?
YOU'RE LATE.

39:51.284 --> 39:52.819
THE JUDGE
IS ON THE BENCH.

39:52.819 --> 39:54.287
JUST GET OUT
OF MY FACE.

39:54.287 --> 39:57.457
MS. YOUNG, I WAS JUST ABOUT
TO GIVE MY RULING.

39:57.457 --> 40:00.160
I'M SORRY, YOUR HONOR.
I WAS WITH MY SON.

40:00.160 --> 40:01.835
YES, I SPOKE WITH THE DOCTOR
THIS MORNING,

40:01.835 --> 40:04.004
AND THEY'RE TELLING ME
THERE'S ABSOLUTELY NO CHANGE.

40:04.004 --> 40:06.873
NO, SIR, HE'S BETTER.
HIS COLOR IS BETTER.

40:06.873 --> 40:09.075
THAT'S NOT SCIENCE,
MS. YOUNG.

40:09.075 --> 40:12.979
AS I HAVE REVIEWED THE CASES
AND CONSULTED WITH ALL CASE LAW

40:12.979 --> 40:17.383
THAT WAS CITED HERE BY COUNSEL
AND EVEN FUTURE COUNSEL,

40:17.383 --> 40:19.886
I'VE SPOKEN
WITH SEVERAL PHYSICIANS,

40:19.886 --> 40:22.956
AND AS THEY ALL THINK
THERE'S A 1% PROBABILITY

40:22.956 --> 40:24.558
FOR ANY TYPE OF RECOVERY

40:24.558 --> 40:28.161
AND BECAUSE THE TAXPAYERS
ARE FOOTING THE BILL

40:28.161 --> 40:30.531
TO KEEP THE LIFE SUPPORT GOING,

40:30.531 --> 40:33.266
I'M GOING TO SIDE
WITH THE FATHER

40:33.266 --> 40:35.536
AND GIVE HIM PERMISSION
TO MAKE THE DECISION

40:35.536 --> 40:38.204
ON WHETHER OR NOT HE SHOULD BE
TAKEN OFF LIFE SUPPORT.

40:38.204 --> 40:39.405
THANK YOU, YOUR HONOR.

40:39.405 --> 40:41.808
W‐W‐WHAT
DOES THAT MEAN?

40:41.808 --> 40:44.077
[ SOBS ]

40:44.077 --> 40:46.212
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

40:46.212 --> 40:47.147
HE WON.

40:47.147 --> 40:48.549
WHAT?
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

40:48.549 --> 40:50.150
HE WON.

40:50.150 --> 40:53.319
WHAT ABOUT
ORGAN DONATION?

40:53.319 --> 40:54.955
POWER OF ATTORNEY
FOR ALL THOSE DECISIONS

40:54.955 --> 40:57.724
IS GRANTED TO THE FATHER.

40:57.724 --> 40:59.926
[ Sobbing ] NO, PLEASE,
YOUR HONOR! WAIT A MINUTE!

40:59.926 --> 41:02.769
CAN I ASK YOU ANYTHING?
CAN I DO SOMETHING, PLEASE?

41:02.769 --> 41:03.970
THAT CAN'T BE RIGHT!

41:03.970 --> 41:06.339
I'M SORRY, MRS. YOUNG.
NO!

41:06.339 --> 41:08.909
CAN I DO SOMETHING DIFFERENT?
PLEASE!

41:08.909 --> 41:12.913
TONY, PLEASE DON'T DO THIS!
TONY, PLEASE DON'T DO THIS!

41:12.913 --> 41:13.914
I'M SORRY IT'S GOT TO BE
LIKE THAT.

41:13.914 --> 41:14.915
TONY, PLEASE,
PLEASE DON'T DO THIS!

41:14.915 --> 41:15.849
I DIDN'T WANT IT
TO BE THIS WAY.

41:15.849 --> 41:17.784
PLEASE ‐‐
NO, NO! STOP, CANDY!

41:17.784 --> 41:19.620
PLEASE, TONY,
DON'T DO THIS!

41:19.620 --> 41:21.622
PLEASE!
JUST LET ME SAY GOODBYE!

41:21.622 --> 41:22.789
IT'S DONE.

41:22.789 --> 41:25.325
PLEASE!

41:28.328 --> 41:31.131
OH! OH, PLEASE.

41:31.131 --> 41:34.267
<i>NEXT WEEK ON "THE HAVES</i>
<i>AND THE HAVE NOTS"...</i>

41:34.267 --> 41:36.136
JEFFERY
THINKS YOU'RE CRAZY.

41:36.136 --> 41:37.638
SHE WANTED TO KILL YOU.

41:39.272 --> 41:40.507
WHAT IS GOING ON HERE?

41:40.507 --> 41:42.275
I'LL TELL YOU AT THE OFFICE.
YOU BETTER.

41:42.275 --> 41:43.376
PLEASE, PLEASE.

41:43.376 --> 41:45.311
PLEASE JUST LET ME SAY
GOODBYE TO HIM.

41:45.311 --> 41:47.147
I'M NOT A BITCH.

41:47.147 --> 41:48.615
THAT'S THE PROBLEM.

41:48.615 --> 41:50.116
HANNA YOUNG,
YOU'RE UNDER ARREST.

41:50.116 --> 41:51.351
FOR WHAT?

41:51.351 --> 41:53.654
HE DIDN'T WAIT FOR ME!

41:53.654 --> 41:56.557
[ SOBS ]

41:56.557 --> 41:58.191
YOU GONNA BE OKAY?

41:58.191 --> 42:00.634
DO I LOOK OKAY?
